re ionizing hydrogen. The\ncorrected, intrinsic ionizing luminosities of the two SSCs younger than ~3 Myr\nare each ~ 5x10^52 s^-1, which is equivalent to each cluster hosting ~5000 O7.5\nV stars. The inferred masses of these SSCs are ~10^6 M_sun.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Jul 2008 20:00:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
